    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with a potent offensive outlook, anchored by **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (78.67) and **Kyle Tucker** (77.10). **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** is our premier play, benefiting from a soft matchup against Jack Kochanowicz, whose 5.35 xERA provides a ceiling-raising environment bolstered by favorable winds. **Kyle Tucker** remains an elite daily start despite a 42% rain risk in his contest against Roupp; his high xwOBA and favorable placement in the order cement his status as an essential anchor. Meanwhile, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56) and **Nasim Nunez** (68.23) are both highly recommended starts, as both capitalize on the significant 6.36 xERA of L\u00f3pez, R, providing the necessary efficiency to attack our scarcest category, stolen bases.\n\nOur most difficult bench decision involved **Marcell Ozuna** (59.22), who fell just shy of the active roster. While **Marcell Ozuna** offers substantial power, his marginal efficiency score relative to the rest of the lineup\u2014specifically compared to the high-upside matchup exploitation offered by **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** and **Nasim Nunez**\u2014led the optimizer to favor the latter duo for their superior situational platoon edges. We are also closely monitoring the 42% rain risk affecting **Andy Pages** and **Kyle Tucker**; should those games be delayed or postponed, **Marcell Ozuna** is the immediate pivot to ensure our game caps remain optimized. Caution is also advised regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" status of **Nolan Schanuel**, **Miguel Vargas**, **Andy Pages**, **Kyle Tucker**, **Josh Lowe**, and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**; should any of these players move down in their respective batting orders, their daily efficiency scores will require re-evaluation before first pitch.",
